hu.elte.txtuml.api

Class ModelString

  • java.lang.Object
    • hu.elte.txtuml.api.ModelType<java.lang.String>
      • hu.elte.txtuml.api.ModelString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelElement, ModelValue

    public class ModelString
extends ModelType<java.lang.String>
    An immutable class representing strings in the model. Use of the Java primitive types and Strings is completely disallowed in the model, except for parameters of constructors and setter methods of ModelType and VariableType classes and their subclasses, and logging methods of Action ( log, logError ).

    Represents: string primitive value

    Usage:

    May be used, for example, as a field of a class, signal parameter or local variable. As it is immutable, it can be used in a style very similar to using primitive values.

    Java restrictions:

    • Instantiate: allowed
    • Define subtype: disallowed

    Example: 

     
 ModelString s = new ModelString("sampletext");
    See the documentation of Model for an overview on modeling in txtUML.
    Author:
    Gabor Ferenc Kovacs
